setInputAndOutputDateFormatToSystem

public static void setInputAndOutputDateFormatToSystem(intradoc.data.DataBinder b)
Updates binder with UserDateFormat field set to the System date/time format. Use getFormattedTimeStamp to then set any date/time fields in the binder. Because UserDateFormat is overridden in the binder by blDateFormat this method also removes blDateFormat from the binder.

getTimeStamp

public static java.lang.String getTimeStamp(java.lang.String format,
                                            java.util.Date d)
                                     throws intradoc.common.ParseStringException
Returns the passed date/time string formatted according to the passed UCM date/time format. Typically this method would be used to add another date to the passed binder before submitting to the server. Setting the format to the existing blDateFormat in the binder will add a date to the binder that matches any existing date fields in the binder. For example, if you create a Date object set to the current time in a UK time zone and pass the format string "MM/dd/yyyy {H:mm:ss [zzz]}!tAmerica/New_York" the output date will be set to the current time in New York.

Parameters:
format -
d -
Returns:
Throws:
intradoc.common.ParseStringException

getRelativeDate

public static java.lang.String getRelativeDate(java.util.Date date)
Takes the given date and returns a string indicating a relative, easily-readable view of the date.
E.g. submitting a date 2 days in the past will return the string '2 days'. 3 weeks in the past will return the string '3 weeks'.

Parameters:
date -
Returns:
the relative date string
